comment_data.body:
There is a one-line change that may achieve the desired behavior:
```diff
diff --git a/src/nvim/terminal.c b/src/nvim/terminal.c
index 499f31454e..3b4bd4f04d 100644
--- a/src/nvim/terminal.c
+++ b/src/nvim/terminal.c
@@ -288,7 +288,7 @@ void terminal_open(Terminal **termpp, buf_T *buf, TerminalOptions opts)
   // force a initial refresh of the screen to ensure the buffer will always
   // have as many lines as screen rows when refresh_scrollback is called
   rv->invalid_start = 0;
-  rv->invalid_end = opts.height;
+  rv->invalid_end = -1;
 
   aco_save_T aco;
   aucmd_prepbuf(&aco, buf);
```
Although it also changes the behavior of cursor position in Normal mode.
